<div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="lai-one"><h2>Celebrating Different Perspectives and Experiences</h2></header>
<div class="lai-no"><div class="lai-img-c lai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="GW Students at the annual Multicultural Student Services Center block party" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/MSSCEvent_OurPriorities_MSSC-Block-Party_UP_WLA_2010-9031.jpg" style="height:720px; width:1080px" /></p>
<figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div>
<div class="lai-copy lai-three"><p>We attract a wide range of students, faculty and staff from around the world with a wealth of viewpoints, perspectives, values and experiences. Understanding and celebrating our differences strengthens our community and encourages problem solving from multiple perspectives.</p>
<p>Our efforts to ensure that everyone receives the support that they need is present throughout the university. From tutoring and disability accommodations to cultural events and volunteer activities, we work to reach and support community members of all interests and backgrounds.</p>
<p>We&rsquo;re answering President Barack Obama&rsquo;s 2014 call to expand opportunities for low-income students through the work of our <a href="/access-success">task force on Access and&nbsp;Success</a>, which has already made strides in bringing students of diverse backgrounds to campus, encouraging attendance and ensuring academic success.</p>
<footer class="call-to-action">&nbsp;</footer></div></div></article></div></div></div>
<hr /><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="rai-one"><h2>Setting You Up for Success</h2></header>
<div class="rai-no"><div class="rai-img-c rai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="GW student interning at the Textile Museum" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/TextileIntern_OurPriorities_TM_Avenir_Center_UP_2016_WLA_6859.jpg" /></p>
<figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div>
<div class="rai-copy rai-three"><p>Life after GW is top of mind well before joining classmates on the National Mall for Commencement. Our <a href="https://careerservices.gwu.edu" target="_blank">Center for Career Services</a> and others throughout the university commit to putting you on a successful, exciting career path through:</p>
<ul><li>more than 12,000 internship opportunities that offer professional development</li><li>career coaching that helps you explore your strengths and interests</li><li>connections to networking and interview opportunities with tips for succeeding in both</li><li>financial support that helps make unpaid internships a feasible choice</li><li>access to a network of more than 275,000 alumni who have ties to leading organizations and businesses around the world</li></ul>
<p>According to a <a href="https://gwtoday.gwu.edu/first-destination-visualization-highlights-continued-success-gw-grads" target="_blank">recent survey</a>, 87 percent of the Class of 2015 reported that within six months of graduation they were employed, pursuing a graduate degree, volunteering or otherwise engaged in a gap year or participating in military service or other activities.</p>
<footer class="call-to-action">&nbsp;</footer></div></div></article></div></div></div>
<hr /><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="lai-one"><h2>Discovering Life-Changing Possibilities</h2></header>
<div class="lai-no"><div class="lai-img-c lai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="GW students and faculty working in a research lab" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/FacultyStudentsLab_OurPriorities_SEH_Bernard_Wood-UP_2015-WLA_1494.jpg" /></p>
<figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div>
<div class="lai-copy lai-three"><p>Our researchers are improving everything from tissue regeneration and drug delivery to developing sustainable ecosystems <a href="/research">through their research efforts</a> in more than 100 countries across the globe. And it&rsquo;s making a difference. We are using robots to help children with autism navigate social situations, creating models that increase understanding of nuclear reactor behavior in earthquakes and partnering with the National Zoo as our lab to&nbsp;study the movements of sea lion foreflippers to advance mechanical innovation.</p>
<p>We&rsquo;re continuing to advance our efforts by utilizing our <a href="/research-resources">research space</a> like Science and&nbsp;Engineering Hall, growing partnerships with federal agencies and multilateral groups to provide research opportunities for students, adding new, impressive faculty and&nbsp;elevating the work of our more than 100 interdisciplinary centers and institutes that connect science and technology, health, public policy, global security and the arts and humanities.</p></div></div></article></div></div></div>
<hr /><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="rai-one"><h2>Doing Good in the World</h2></header>
<div class="rai-no"><div class="rai-img-c rai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="GW students working outside during Freshman Day of Service" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/FDOSTrees_OurPriorities_FDOS_UP_2014-WLA_8295.jpg" /></p>
<figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div>
<div class="rai-copy rai-three"><p>Our commitment to service and civic engagement is visible throughout our campuses, the D.C. community and around the world. Our students challenge one another to use their skills to lead, volunteer and innovate through programs led by the <a href="https://serve.gwu.edu" target="_blank">Honey W. Nashman Center for Civic Engagement and Public Service</a>, more than 70 service-learning courses and other activities throughout the university.</p>
<p>We meet community needs beyond our campuses through many programs, including:</p>
<ul><li>support and tutoring for youth in the D.C. community</li><li>volunteer opportunities around the world during spring and summer break, focused on topics from sustainability and labor rights to education signature events like Freshman Day of Service and Martin Luther King, Jr. Day of Service</li></ul>
<footer class="call-to-action">&nbsp;</footer></div></div></article></div></div></div>
<hr /><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="lai-one"><h2>Welcoming Those Who Have Served</h2></header>
<div class="lai-no"><div class="lai-img-c lai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="GW veteran students during a NROTC commissioning ceremony" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/VeteransNationalMall_OurPriorities_nrotc_comissioning-UP-2015-ZWM-3880.jpg" style="height:720px; width:1080px" /></p>
<figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div>
<div class="lai-copy lai-three"><p>A commitment to service extends beyond coursework and volunteering for our veteran students and students with military experience.</p>
<p>We welcome them to GW to use their dedication, leadership skills and lessons learned to find a fulfilling career path.</p>
<p>Through <a href="https://services.military.gwu.edu/" target="_blank">Military and Veteran Student Services</a>, we ensure that veterans, active-duty military and their children receive the support that they need to get an education and find their passion.</p>
<p>Since 2013, military and veteran enrollment has increased by 500 students, with more than 1,800 military students, veterans and their dependents attending GW during the 2015-2016 academic year.</p></div></div></article></div></div></div>
<hr /><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="rai-one"><h2>Advocating for Buff, Blue and Green</h2></header>
<div class="rai-no"><div class="rai-img-c rai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="Green roof on GW's Science &amp; Engineering Hall" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/GreenRoof_OurPriorities_sehkiosk-july-UP-2015-WLA-7228.jpg" style="height:720px; width:1080px" /></p>
<figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div>
<div class="rai-copy rai-three"><p>Sustainability is part of everything we do. From academics and research to daily operations and student engagement, we&rsquo;re working to create a brighter future for our students, community and the planet. Our efforts are visible on our campuses from LEED-certified buildings to alternative energy solutions, including our Solar Walk on the <a href="/virginia-science-technology-campus">Virginia Science &amp; Technology Campus</a>.</p>
<p>Our students know that their dedication to the planet will impact their future, so we&rsquo;ve developed sustainability-focused classes and research programs, including a sustainability minor, that will help students incorporate sustainable practices into a range of career paths.</p>
<p>We also engage the world through sustainability policy and governance and bring some of the brightest minds to our campuses to do so. Initiatives through the <a href="http://sustainability.gwu.edu" target="_blank">Office of Sustainability and Sustainability Collaborative</a>, such as Planet Forward and the GW Solar Institute, are implemented in partnership with stakeholders from across the university.</p></div></div></article></div></div></div>    </div>
